Special Test Requirements:




Test Date: 11/15/2013



Comments: Note1: In ""PwrLmtFuncCr_Per1"" function, out of range value is given to variables ""k_KeStdTemp_VpRadpS_f32"", ""t_MtrEnvTblY_MtrNm_u5p11[14]"" and ""EstKe_VpRadpS_f32""
to cover the paths ""(k_KeStdTemp_VpRadpS_f32 > 0)=FALSE"" in Test case 2.3(P) , ""(MRFMtrTrq_MtrNm_T_f32 > (float(8.8)))=TRUE"" in Test case 2.6(P) and
""(TrqEnvLmt4_MtrNm_T_f32< TLimitMaxCurr_MtrNm_T_f32)=FALSE"" in Test case 2.5(P) respectively and due to this "PwrLmtFuncCr_TrqEnvLmt1_MtrNm_M_f32" variable value is going out of range.
Note2: In ""PwrLmtFuncCr_Per1"" function, out of range value is given to variable ""t_MtrEnvTblY_MtrNm_u5p11[14]"" in TS2.11
to cover ""(MRFMtrTrq_MtrNm_T_f32 < (float(-8.8)))=TRUE"" path and due to this "PwrLmtFuncCr_TrqEnvLmt1_MtrNm_M_f32" variable value is going out of range..
Note3: Range of "PwrLmtFuncCr_MinStdOpLmt_MtrNm_M_f32" and "MRFMtrTrqCmd_MtrNm_f32" variable is ""-8.8 to 8.8"".
But in ""PwrLmtFuncCr_Per1"" function, for few testcases output value of ""PwrLmtFuncCr_MinStdOpLmt_MtrNm_M_f32"" is +/-8.800048828125 and of variable "MRFMtrTrqCmd_MtrNm_f32" is "+/-8.80000019073486" which is exceptable as it is within the listed tolerance(i.e 0.00048828125).
